name: I4 Bullseye Data File
summary: Learn about .BUL files and view a list of programs that open them.

content: BUL files are typically created by I4, a biomedical image processing program used in researching heart-related activity. However, BUL files may be created by JSim, a program used to build and analyze numeric models related to biomedicine and physiology.
NOTE: The National Simulation Resource (NSR) Physiome Project is a research effort that began at the University of Washington Department of Bioengineering.
